title: The Case Against Immigration (1996) by Roy Howard Beck
description:
The Case Against Immigration - The Moral, Economic, Social, and Environmental Reasons for Reducing U.S. Immigration Back to Traditional Levels (1996) by Roy Howard Beck.pdf

Beck's book redefines a flashpoint issue for America's future and for the 1996 elections, showing how current high immigration--far beyond traditional levels--benefits mainly the rich, and why immigration rates must be drastically lowered to ensure that America remains a society of opportunity for all its citizens, including recent immigrants.

287 pages
Publisher: W W Norton & Co Inc; 1 edition (April 1996)
Language: English
ISBN-10: 0393039153
ISBN-13: 978-0393039153
